Where all the intricacies of the airship reside in. There exists four massive quadrants on each corner of the room and the chassis, which is semi transparent with a white tint, encapsulates the complex machinery that runs the operations of many of the ship's necessary components. Unsurprisingly, its exterior is extremely durable to protect the fragile internals. On each of those pillars, there is a small panel to the side as well as an outline of what seems to be a door. From the looks of it, the panel can grant access to the insides of the chassis with the proper authorization, mainly for the purposes of maintenance. Other than that, there's nothing too crazy going on inside this room, other than some vents scattered around the room to help aerate the engine room.
